### Enhancements

* Defer imports of heavy dependencies (`unearth`, `build`, `installer`, `conda_index`) in `conda_pypi.plugin`, the `install`/`convert`/`index` CLI subcommands, and the `external-packages` health check until they are actually needed.

* Add a Ruff `TID253` rule banning module-level imports of `unearth`, `build`, `installer`, and `conda_index` to prevent this class of startup-time regression from being reintroduced. Files whose sole purpose is wrapping these libraries are annotated with `# noqa: TID253`; files under `tests/` are exempted via `per-file-ignores`. 

